Uses of Responses in jsl.modeling
 

Methods in jsl.modeling that return Responses
 Responses ModelElement.makeResponses()
          This method should be implemented by subclasses that want to return Responses especially after an experiment is completed Can be overridden by sub-classes to define instances of Responses Unless overridden calls to makeRespones() will return null, implying that the ModelElement does not have Responses.
